modules.description: Parses operating system information from user agent strings into structured data. It provides functions to initialize a parser, execute parsing, and compare or display results. The module handles version components like major, minor, and patch releases for OS families.

This module parses device information from user agent strings, extracting the device family, brand, and model. It provides functions to initialize a parser, parse a user agent string into a result, and compare, print, or convert result values. Use it to identify mobile devices, tablets, or desktop systems from HTTP user agent headers.

This module parses user agent strings into structured version information. It supports initializing a parser and extracting the browser family and semantic version components (major, minor, patch) from a user agent string. It is used to identify client browser details in web applications or analytics tools.

This module processes user agent strings to extract structured browser, operating system, and device information. It provides functions to initialize a parser, parse user agent strings, and retrieve detailed results including browser family, OS version, and device model. It is used to analyze HTTP user agent headers in web applications or analytics platforms.
